Before answering, let’s sort out some misconceptions…

You know, on how women who are models and women on Instagram are thick, are not smart, got no brains, and only show their body because that’s all they can do really?

He must have left her because she was just sex

You know, slut shaming women as nothing good but for sex, and all they are good at is showing their figures.

  • Fluent in French, Russian, and German.

Has a Master's degree in chemical engineering from Leeds University.

  • Has a J.D. from Villanova University School of Law and a Ph.D. in Clinical Psychology from Drexel University.

What that tells us, is these women have guts. They could easily have done what many do and follow their social peers to be accepted and fit in but instead, they followed what made them feel alive, satisfied and happy.

They probably already felt what it’s like, after all they went on that path already, did their degrees and realised, they are not happy, and wanted to follow their own path no matter if people judge them.

I could go on and on and on and there’s too many examples.

Now to your questions…

Yes, he’s doing what everyone does but we like to pretend we are better than someone else. We love to say that we are better and not superficial as models and hot women on instagram.

We’ll slut shame, call women as “not good for sex only,” and how they just got nothing else but a hot body and slut shame men too with, “men just see women as sex,” and “players, bad boys, jerks,” on it goes.

It’s like people got to have people to be like them when we’re in a world with different people, different beliefs, different desires, needs, wants and yet we got people trying to label them to make themselves in some group to say they are better than them.

All such folks doing is like everyone else - trying to find meaning of their life in the world they are in and one way is to say “us” and “them.”

It’s nothing new. It’s been going for centuries.

Yeah, we all have a bit of Narcissim in us, acting superior. People got to follow our rules, our norms or they are rebels, they are bad people, they are sluts, whores, too easy, players, bad boys and jerks.

No one put a head in women or men to date anyone and yet, we still look to blame someone or judge someone, because being a victim or being someone who feels they are better, makes us all feel so good.

Reality is, we all got cracks in our lives, wearing masks and most of us charade around the world being someone else, scared that if we don’t do what our social peers say, we will be judged as sluts, whores, too easy, plays and bad boys, and…superficial.

We love to say the reason is the model is superficial and just for sex and he left for someone who has more blah blah blah.

So let’s look at a different angle…

  • How do we know, that he had challenges being in a relationship with a woman who is attractive, a model and felt insecure because he knew and seen, wherever he walked, so many men looked at her, gave her attention even when he is walking and being with her?

You think good looking men are not insecure?

I know many are very insecure you won’t believe. In fact, I got a que of them I am coaching and some cannot eve approach a woman out fear of rejection.

Some who who are dating an attractive women are so full of fear of losing her, grown possessive and jealous that they can’t even recognise who they are. Some get so worked up because guys are staring her.

The damage they did to their relationship will bewilder you.

  • How do we know he just couldn’t take it and felt that this is going to be this way all time and it caused problems in the relationship because he made it an issue?
  • How do we know he wasn’t jealous, possessive and it caused heartache for her and she had enough and it wasn’t he who walked away but she did.
  • How do we know, he went for the average looking pianist because he felt safer and less insecure? That he knows every guy is not going to hit on her or stare at her when he’s walking about with her?

But we don’t think that can be the story.

Oh we love the story to make us look amazing, so smarter, so whatever because we’re average looking and so, let’s s call any woman who is attractive a slut, a whore, too easy, just for sex and if it wasn’t for her body, she can’t do anything else.

We start answering from our reality, our religious, cultural, twisted minds because we love to believe that story to make ourselves feel better…

“Yeah, these women are shallow and not good for only sex. That’s why he left.”

“Yeah, the reason is the model was not smart, intellectual so he now wants a smarter woman.”

“Yeah these women who show their body got only that going for them.”

  • How about that he experienced things in life, he got different values and so he is looking for something else? No, not better but what is compatible with the man he is today?
  • Or she changed and realised he’s not for her and felt it was time to move on?

For example, what we believed in as a person 20 years ago, we don’t believe in it anymore.

Or our perception has changed and even some of our values that we’re more relaxed to laugh about it, not take it too serious and grown to now see much of what we might believe can change.

This has nothing to do with the woman who is a model.

This has nothing to do with the other woman who is average looking professional pianist.

This is to do, with what we all go through.

That we change and sometimes we desire something else, that sometimes we do grow apart from someone else, due to experiences and due to wanting different things in our lives.

But to say that the reason that man married an average looking woman who is a “professional pianist” because the model woman was nothing but for sex for looks, is emotional bias.

It’s not talking into consideration that maybe the man feels unsafe, insecure that he’s with an attractive woman and she gets attention far more than he does as a man.

That he realised, what women realise - that their looks, curves, the man also with his his size of his dick, his income and looks cannot control, fix and change a person to live a life they want.

How about we see that perspective than slut shaming women who are models and men too.

Maybe she didn’t want to be married.

Maybe she didn’t want what he wanted.

Maybe he had expectations and realised those expectations will not happen for him with her, and she didn’t know about these expectations. He realised, it’s time to move on.

Maybe she had expectations but realised those expectations were not going to happen and as time went by, she realised it’s time to move on.

We all like to believe in “us,” and “them.”

We all like to put some people in boxes and labels, to make ourselves feel we are better, we are not shallow, we are not superficial, far superior because we don’t go for looks.

No, we are perfect!

But really..

We are no different.

In reality, we choose what is best for us for that particular time in our life.

That’s why the man went for an average looking woman.

He’s looking for compatibility for the man he is today.

He went for what he desires now in his life and that doesn’t take away anything from the woman who is a model.
